						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">nocash wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">&gt; Note, / replaced with _, due to the way variable names in C work.<br />Now it looks even more confusing... the !&amp;&amp;|| stuff already confused me a lot. I guess it means NOT, AND, OR, but I never figured out why one would replace that words by punctuation marks.</div><br /><br />This whole NOT, AND, OR, with !&amp;&amp;||, is kind of second nature to C/C++/PHP/Java/C# programmers. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />  That !&amp;&amp;|| is Logical stuff.  Bitwise NOT,AND,OR is ~&amp;|. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

