					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">nocash wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I never figured out why one would replace that words by punctuation marks.</div><br /><br />Terseness. Same reason for basic math.<br /><br />Group three plus seven Endgroup times Group six plus five Endgroup equals one hundred and ten.<br /><br />Or (3+7)*(6+5)=110.<br /><br />In caitsith's case, &amp; and | would have the same effect. Doubtful short circuiting behavior matters much here.<br />Bonus points: come up with C++ operators for NAND, NOR, XNOR that are not combinations of the others :P</div>

